<s> In the absence of a specific server request for any minimum return count, the proxy cannot know if the report is worth sending.  </s>
<s> Some servers may not believe that a return connection is worth the overhead of receiving a 1/0 report, just as some servers may insist on seeing a 0/0 report to know that the proxy's 'best-effort' is succeeding.  </s>
<s> perhaps the initial negotiation could contain a count-range meter header from the proxy indicating the bounds (both hi and low) it is willing to report for, and the server response could return min and max values in that range that represents the reporting interval.  </s>
